<center>Star Heavens of the Dioscuri Volume 1 - The Revived
Myth</center>

<center>This is the record of the battle between the "Gods
of Mythology" resurrected in modern times and the twin girls
who stood up to them-</center>

The academy city "Kamuiyama Town," where talented
individuals from various fields are gathered...

Living there are the twin girls, "Kirara Hoshizora" and
"Sarara Hoshizora".

Although they lost their mother at a young age, the always
cheerful and positive Kirara created a bright atmosphere,
while the calm and reliable Sarara took on the role of
mother, supporting their life.

Their father, "Kousuke Hoshizora," a historian, watched over
them kindly, and the family lived peaceful, albeit modest,
days.

There were also the twin brothers living nearby, "Reiki
Tsukioka" and "Reito Tsukioka,"...

the interactions with "Yui Minazuki," whom Kirara and Sarara
adored like a younger sister, and their school life.

Their everyday life was always the same, ordinary but
enjoyable...

The girls never doubted that this daily life would continue
forever.

An intruder appeared in a secret room hidden by Kousuke in
the basement of the Hoshizora household.

The man, ignoring Kousuke's attempts to stop him, broke the
seal on a "box" placed there.
Lights flew out of the box, and the man also disappeared.

As Kirara and Sarara were walking through the shopping
district on their way home from school, a mysterious ring
fell from the sky. A voice echoed from the ring-
"Young girl, would you lend me your strength?"

The owner of the voice introduced themselves as the mythical
heroes "Polydeuces" and "Castor," informing them that the
gods had revived and were about to attack people.
To the incredulous pair, the heroes showed a certain visual.

The scene where "Heracles," a hero resurrected by taking
over a human body...
happened to encounter Yui Minazuki and attacked her.

"Humans are just servants to gods and heroes, so just
quietly do as you're told!"

The giant hero uttered selfish words while trampling over
the small girl's body.

In their desperation to save their beloved Yui, Kirara and
Sarara heard the heroes inside the ring pleading for them to
lend their power.

To save Yui, they accepted the offer and embraced the power
of the heroes...

The moment they did, their forms changed into those clad in
divine robes (robes).

The heroes were puzzled because they were supposed to have
borrowed human bodies and resurrected in their past forms
like Heracles, but instead, only Kirara and Sarara's clothes
had changed while they remained in their own forms.

However, there was no time to ponder the reason now, as the
twin girls resolved to fight Heracles themselves.

When they reached Heracles and Yui, what they saw was the
battered figure of a small girl.
"Why... why would you do something so terrible...!"

Driven by anger, Kirara struck out. Her fist, imbued with
the power of the gods "Divine Spirit Power," made Heracles'
massive body stagger.
And so began the battle between the hero and the girls.

Kirara aimed for Heracles' right knuckle, which housed his
heroic power. Having heard that taking it could revert him
back to a human, she fought on equal terms with the giant
hero with support from Sarara, who sent instructions through
their shared Divine Spirit Power.

The coordination between Kirara, who had originally learned
martial arts, and Sarara, who excelled in analytical skills,
was so impressive that it didn't seem like their first
battle.

Even so, they could not reach the power of Heracles, a hero
seasoned in battle.

The defeated Kirara was assaulted by the big man's desire.
Entangled by tentacles spawned from an egg held by Heracles,
the girl was toyed with and etched with unknown pleasures
without any means to resist.

And then, the man approached the other girl who had fallen
and couldn't move.

If nothing was done, Sarara would be in danger too. The
moment Kirara realized this-
In her hazy consciousness, the girl stood up once again...

She overwhelmed Heracles with her combat strength, relying
on that immense Divine Spirit Power.

The moment she was about to deliver the finishing blow to
the unconscious big man, Kirara stopped at the sound of
Sarara's voice calling for restraint.

Having removed the knuckle from the fallen Heracles, Kirara
then lost consciousness and collapsed.

The twin girls awoke in a hospital bed. There, they were
greeted by the cheerful smiling face of Yuno.

Although Kirara and Sarara were concerned about the wounds
on their hearts and bodies, their demeanor did not show any
signs of the humiliation they remembered.

The girls went home with Takato, who had come to pick them
up from the hospital.

Among the gods, a secret pact was made upon learning that
Heracles had been defeated.

"The one who defeats them will be granted dominion over the
world," it was declared.
Kirara's heart ached from the scars of humiliation.
Sarara could only watch, unable to do anything.

Without any time to bask in the afterglow of their first
battle's victory, the wheels of fate began to turn for the
twin girls.

<center>Star Heavens of the Dioscuri Volume 2 - Stirrings of
the Gods</center>

<center>This is the record of the battle between the
"Mythological Gods" resurrected in modern times and the twin
girls who stood against them-</center>

The seal of the mythological gods was broken, and the hero
Heracles, resurrected in modern times, was repelled by
Kirara and Sarara with the help of the twin heroes Pollux
and Castor.

Several days had passed since that battle, but Kirara and
Sarara's surroundings were completely peaceful, as if
nothing had happened.

Having resolved to fight the gods, they were constantly
tense, not knowing when the battle would come, so the
complete lack of incidents was anticlimactic.

On this holiday, the two decided to take a look around the
city with the heroes, partly to satisfy their desire to
learn about the current world.

"...The people of this world seem content. Various things
overflow in the city..."

"In our time, only a part of the royalty was wealthy, while
other people were forced into harsh labor every day..."

The heroes from the mythological era expressed their deep
impressions upon seeing the state of modern people's lives.

"The power of gods is no longer needed... Was 'that
person's' words correct?"

"'That person'? Was there someone who predicted this would
happen long ago?"

Kirara showed interest in Castor's words, which she heard
through her connection with Sarara.

"Yes... There was a god who excelled in foresight...
Ultimately, the gods went into slumber because of that god's
words."

Fighting against the resurrected gods... It was still not
something that felt real to the two girls.

However, the fact that the mythological hero Heracles had
appeared and their friends had been attacked...

And the fact that they had defeated Heracles with the help
of fellow heroes Pollux and Castor meant that the upcoming
battles against the gods to be resurrected were unavoidable.
The heroes residing within them began to recount the past.

In ancient times... there was an era when gods ruled over
the world.

The gods tamed the raging atmosphere with their immense
power, calmed the furious seas, and brought fertility to the
land.

Eventually, harmony emerged on earth, and stability was seen
in the cycle of life and matter. Amongst the gods, some
sought to seize control of the world.

And so, conflict began among the gods. After generations of
strife, those who stood at the pinnacle of the gods were
called the Twelve Olympians.

As time passed and the earth no longer needed the power of
gods, beings without power began to emerge among them.

Under divine rule, humans built civilizations and gradually
increased their numbers.
Thus, an era where gods and humans coexisted came to be.

The gods, possessing too much power, could only see humans
as their slaves, forgetting that they were once of the same
existence...

The gods granted blessings to those who worshipped them.
However, they mercilessly punished those who did not worship
or worshipped other gods.

Eventually, among humans and heroes born from both gods and
humans, some began to question this status quo.

In such a climate, a great war broke out where men and gods
clashed.

A small quarrel among goddesses sparked this war known as
the "Trojan War," which involved heroes and people alike,
resulting in a tragic bloodshed.

And then... as a result of that war, some among the gods
began to assert this:

"Humans and the world can now live on their own strength.
Our role as overseers is over."
"Let us sleep until the world needs our power again."

The majority of Olympian gods at their zenith could not
accept this, leading to a final conflict between those on
Olympus' side and those who sought to create a world
governed by humans.

The heroes residing within Kirara and Sarara could not
provide an answer.

Having lost their lives in the midst of battle, they did not
witness the conclusion of the divine war.

Gods and heroes with strong divine powers do not immediately
perish in spirit even after physical death due to being
enveloped in divine power.

If there is a special divine instrument capable of accepting
divine power like "Dioscuroi Robe," it is possible for
spirits to reside within it.

Thus, gods and heroes only truly 'die' when both their body
and spirit are extinguished.

Pollux, Castor, and Hercules, upon facing death, entrusted
their spirits to the "Dioscuroi Robe" and "Dynamis Keir" and
fell into slumber.
To await the time of their next awakening...

"I remember... The gods who sided with humans said this,
didn't they? 'Let us sleep until the world needs our power
again.'"

"Does the revival of Castor-san and the others mean that
'the time' has come? Does it mean an era where gods rule
over humans is approaching?"
Castor slowly answered Kirara and Sarara's question.

"I do not know... However, we do not wish for a world to
suffer at the whim of the gods as in the past."

"For that reason, we must stop the gods who seek to rule
over humans."

"But... even if you say stop them, gods are... strong,
right? Can we really fight and win?"

The one who answered Sarara's doubt was neither the twin
heroes nor Hercules.

Before Kirara and Sarara appeared a man who harbored within
him one of the twelve Olympians, "Ares."

Ares revealed to them the content of a secret pact made
among the gods.

"Whoever defeats you without harming this world will gain
the right to rule it."
The shocking truth changed the expressions of the two girls.

However, this was also advantageous for them. If they fought
and defeated the gods, they could restore peace without
anyone else getting hurt.

It was a harsh path for the twin girls, but it seemed like a
ray of hope shone on their upcoming battles.

Ares, showing his overwhelming power, declared war on them,
stating that with their current strength, they were far from
reaching the power of "gods" who surpassed heroes.

Ares, who loved battle above all else, gave time to the two
girls who were still unaccustomed to the power of heroes,
wishing for a serious match.

Someone was scouting this encounter between Ares and the
twin girls. It was "Kaidou Kyoushirou," a representative of
Kamiyama Town and also the president of the managing
corporation. He too was a man who harbored a "god" within
him.

The man who knew all the data of every resident in town
could roughly predict which hosts the gods and heroes had
chosen.

The quiet struggle for world domination among the gods
worked in the man's favor.

In order to become strong enough to reach "god" level in
limited time, Kirara and Sarara decided to start by learning
more about divine spirit power and visited "Kanami Tetsuji,"
a teacher at Kamiyama Academy who harbored the god
"Hephaestus."

The god persuaded by Kanami, who knew Kirara and Sarara
well, promised to cooperate with them.

Hephaestus spoke of conceptual things regarding divine
spirit power.

Gods, heroes, and humans are composed of three elements:
"body," "spirit," and "divine spirit power."

Gods and heroes can maintain their "spirit" through strong
"divine spirit power" even after losing their "body," and it
is possible for them to be resurrected by finding a new
"body."

Normally, "spirit" and "divine spirit power" cannot be
separated, and even if borrowing a host's "body," only
"divine spirit power" separated from "spirit" moving under
the control of Kirara and others is an impossibility.

Normally, multiple vast divine spirit powers cannot coexist
within a single host's body; if they did, they could
interfere with each other and possibly annihilate each
other. The case of Kirara receiving both Pollux's and
Hercules's divine spirit powers is quite an irregular
example.

And Hephaestus told them that in order to become stronger in
a short period of time, it is important to "know one's own
strength."
Kirara remembered someone's words upon hearing this.
"Control your own power, know your own strength."

These were the words of Kirara's martial arts master, the
priest of Kamiyama Shrine, "Koumyouin Yousei."

Kirara and Sarara decided to rely on Yousei and visited
Kamiyama Shrine.

Yousei and his sister "Hazuki" already knew all the
circumstances and had anticipated their visit.

The two changed their appearance before Kirara and Sarara.
Yes, they too harbored gods within them: "Apollo" and
"Artemis."

The two gods who did not wish for a return of the divine war
and hoped to live quietly in the new era promised to help
with Kirara and Sarara's intensive training.

Thus, Kirara would receive special training from Yousei and
Apollo, while Sarara would be trained by Hazuki and Artemis.

Deciding to stay at Kamiyama Shrine for their training, the
two girls would also attend school from there for a week.

During that time, Kirara encountered a boy from the same
class, "Amagawa Tsubasa." Tsubasa had always admired Kirara,
but at this time, she only interacted with him as one of her
friends.

From that day on, the twin girls began their special
training. Kirara's training aimed to master the control of
divine spirit power from Apollo and the technique "Hanten
Shou" of the "Koumyouin-style Kenjutsu" from Yousei.

Meanwhile, Sarara devoted all her effort to mastering the
technique "Lunar Brid" using the bow passed down from
Artemis.

While the two were engrossed in their training, Kounin
visited the forge of Hephaestus.

Kounin confessed to Hephaestus that he had been guarding
Pandora's box, which sealed the gods, and requested that it
be made usable again.

Kounin was tormented by the reality that the gods had
started a game-like pursuit targeting his daughters.
However, if the gods were to rise up all at once, a return
to divine warfare would be inevitable.

All Kounin could do now was to watch over the two while
preparing for the worst-case scenario.

And then, after the promised week had passed... the two
girls once again confronted Ares.

Ares began by unleashing his subordinate gods to gauge the
growth of the two, but Kirara and Sarara easily repelled
them. They had certainly acquired the power to fight against
the gods.

To counter Ares's immense power, Kirara and Sarara deployed
their twin-specific divine technique "Eternal Bond (Link)."

Even though their individual powers were not a match for
Ares, they fought on equal terms with the power of their
divine technique that synchronized Sarara's spatial
recognition ability with Kirara's combat strength.

Then, taking advantage of their teamwork, Kirara lured Ares
into a charge and unleashed her newly mastered ultimate move
"Hanten Shou."

However, this technique was read by Ares, the god of war,
and avoided...
And in return, Kirara received a painful counterattack.

Still, when Kirara was about to give up, Sarara conveyed a
secret plan for reversal.

Sarara, believing in Kirara, imbued all her divine spirit
power into an arrow.

Believing in Sarara, Kirara once again took the stance for
"Hanten Shou."
Ares unleashed his greatest technique at Kirara.

Sarara fired her most powerful "Lunar Brid" at Ares, who
easily dodged it. However, this was all within Sarara's

Ares dodged the arrow of light which Kirara caught and

Meanwhile, at Kamiyama Shrine, Poseidon was attacking Hazuki

Artemis fought advantageously against Poseidon who used

However, she was defeated by Poseidon's water phantoms with

Poseidon let his tentacle monster capture the goddess

Poseidon relentlessly toyed with his captured prey.

As Artemis lost consciousness and reverted to Hazuki's form,

Yousei, who had gone to watch over Kirara and Sarara's

Yousei = Apollo was furious that his precious sister had
been defiled. In his overwhelming anger, he recklessly
attacked Poseidon.

If he had maintained his usual calmness, he would never have
been outpaced. However, he was easily deceived by the mist
illusions and received a blow from behind that brought him

As Kirara and Sarara were resting from their exhaustion
after fighting Ares and were about to head home...
Poseidon's water prison captured them both.

The two nearly lost consciousness as they had almost
exhausted their divine spirit power and could do nothing...

At that moment, driven by a single-minded desire to protect
Sarara, Kirara awakened once more and shattered the water
prison with tremendous divine spirit power.

Impressed yet surprised by Kirara's power, Poseidon decided
to test Sarara's power next and unleashed his tentacle beast
god.

Sarara's screams as she was captured by the tentacles
unconsciously triggered Kirara's response, blowing away the

However, having used up all her strength, Kirara collapsed
on the spot.

Sarara could not stop Poseidon as he picked up Kirara to
take her away; she didn't even have the strength left to
stand up.

When Kirara awoke, she found herself on a rocky islet

the rocks with cold chains.
In front of her was Poseidon, wearing a cold smile.

To discover the true nature of the power hidden within
Kirara, the man released the tentacle beast god once again.

The girl's scream echoed through the night sea, cutting
through the sound of the waves.
